Based on the reference materials and detailed specifications, here's the complete implementation of the required functions:

```cpp
#include <hexi/pmc/buffer_adaptor.h>
#include <hexi/shared.h>
#include <vector>
#include <cstdint>

bool check_can_write_seek(hexi::pmc::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<std::byte>>& buffer) {
    return buffer.can_write_seek();
}

void seek_write_position(hexi::pmc::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<std::byte>>& buffer, hexi::buffer_seek direction, std::size_t offset) {
    buffer.write_seek(direction, offset);
}

void update_header_at_position(hexi::pmc::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<std::byte>>& buffer, uint32_t header_value) {
    // Save current write position by seeking to current position (using absolute seek with current size)
    std::size_t current_position = buffer.size(); // Get current write position

    // Write header at beginning
    buffer.write_seek(hexi::buffer_seek::sk_absolute, 0);
    buffer.write(&header_value, sizeof(header_value));

    // Write body data
    std::string body_data = "This is the body content";
    buffer.write(body_data.data(), body_data.size());

    // Seek back to beginning to update header
    buffer.write_seek(hexi::buffer_seek::sk_absolute, 0);
    buffer.write(&header_value, sizeof(header_value));

    // Restore original write position
    buffer.write_seek(hexi::buffer_seek::sk_absolute, current_position);
}
```

## Explanation:

1. **`check_can_write_seek`**: Directly calls the `can_write_seek()` method from the `buffer_adaptor` class, which delegates to the underlying buffer's `can_write_seek()` method.

2. **`seek_write_position`**: Calls the `write_seek()` method with the provided direction and offset parameters, utilizing the `buffer_seek` enum values.

3. **`update_header_at_position`**:
   - Saves the current write position using `buffer.size()` (which returns the current write position)
   - Uses absolute seeking (`sk_absolute`) to position at the beginning (offset 0)
   - Writes the header value using the `write()` method
   - Writes sample body data
   - Seeks back to the beginning to update the header with the same value
   - Restores the original write position

The implementation follows the exact specifications provided, using the appropriate methods and enums from the Hexi library as documented in the reference materials.

